-- Indonesian Attorney General Soedjono C. Atmonegoro said here that an investigation on the wealth of former government officials, including former President Soeharto and his family, was going on.
-- The Indonesian National Land Agency's Jambi office has uncovered evidence of former President Soeharto's allegedly ill-gotten wealth in Central Sumatra Province alone.
He refused to disclose the details, saying that the investigation needs a long time.
The Indonesian government has set up two teams to investigate alleged corruption by Soeharto as well as his wealth.
Meanwhile, State Secretary/Minister Akbar Tanjung reiterated the government's seriousness in investigating Soeharto's wealth.
